	<td class="alt2">
	
		
			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>The Future of Charm</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" color="" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Am I the only one who remembers the BIG charm nerf almost a year ago.  It seems we as a community made a decision not to complain about the changes lest an even more dire nerf be put into play.  The complaints sputtered out but, SOE's desire and need to NERF Charm did not end.  Which is why we ended up with the situation in LDoN where charm is about 95% Nerfed to non existence.  Yet even then there has been continued silence from a community either indifferent or afraid to confront the issue of Charm and it's future in EQ.  I personally don't want to see Charm wither and die as a Tactic but,  I also see as mobs scale in power charm too scales with them in a way that unbalances the game.  The problem is with our silence or indifference changes are being and have been made to charm without any community input.  I would loath to see us go into the new expansion GoD and, find out that the status quo establish in LDoN is further carried on.  Charming classes deserve a solution that maintains an ability that is effective and fun yet balanced and viable.  It is time to open up a dialogue so that the people who enjoy charming can be heard.  Don't be silent.  It's your Future.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
			<div>
				__________________<br />
