	<td class="alt2">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Ok,<br />
heres one thing I reallllly dont like about charm, and it applies to direcharmed pets too. And thats how they totally lose any agro they've built up on a mob when the hate list of the mob exceeds 4. <br />
With 4 (say 3 player characters and the pet) the DC mob can and will hold aggro if the rest of the players are reasonably careful. As soon as you add another person/pet etc to the hate list then the aggro from the pet is *complately* wiped and it will make a beeline for whichever player was currently next highest on the hate list (even if they'd barely generated any hate).<br />
Things I really dont like about this are:<br />
<br />
 - it's illogical - why should there be a critical number of creatures/players on a mobs hate list that makes it suddenly forget about the charmed pet? <br />
<br />
 - it's arbituary... why 4? why not allow 6, or just 2 or whatever on the hate list before this happens?<br />
<br />
- it's open to griefing. If you're using a DC pet tank in a grp of 3, everything is ok, however if another player comes close by and gets himself on the hate list then the mob is going to forget the tank and start carving up the group.. <br />
<br />
Most of all tho, it just doesnt make sense to me, and although it may not impact on that many peoples playing styles, and hence why theres not that much complaining about it, I am personally very disappointed that its been changed in this way. I hate having to turn down friends from grouping and trying to explain to them that I cant add in another caster to our group because it will put the group over the critical limit of people that can be on a mobs hate list before it forgets that the DC pet is the tank! (its a bit of a mouthful to explain too... <img src="http://thedruidsgrove.org/forums/images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" />  )</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
